      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Seagram Company said yesterday that it had narrowed the review on the United States account of three brands -- Crown Royal whisky, Captain Morgan rums and Myers's rum -- to three agencies from eight. The brands, with billings estimated at $14 million to $16 million, were handled by DDB Needham Worldwide in New York until that agency was dismissed in June.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Seagram Company said yesterday that it had narrowed the review on the United States account of three brands -- Crown Royal whisky, Captain Morgan rums and Myers's rum -- to three agencies from eight. The brands, with billings estimated at $14 million to $16 million, were handled by DDB Needham Worldwide in New York until that agency was dismissed in June.</p>
        <p>Chris Tofalli, a spokesman for Seagram in New York, identified the finalists as Ayer Inc., Grey Advertising and Waring &amp; LaRosa, all of New York. The agencies eliminated, also all based in New York, were Chiat/Day; Jordan, McGrath, Case &amp; Taylor; Ogilvy &amp; Mather; TBWA Advertising, and Young &amp; Rubicam. A decision is expected next month, Mr. Tofalli said.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
